# Time Tracking Fixes

## Issues to Fix

### 1. Timeline Not Showing New Entries ❌
**Problem**: New entries don't appear on timeline after creation
**Root Cause**: Need to investigate if entries are being created correctly and if timeline is filtering them properly
**Solution**: Verify `timelineEntries` filter in [TimePageClient](file:///c:/Users/oleks/dashboard-app/src/components/time/time-page-client.tsx#92-482) includes all work entries

### 2. Breaks Not Appearing ❌  
**Problem**: Gaps between entries don't show as break rows
**Current Logic**: Line 701 in [TimeEntriesList](file:///C:/Users/oleks/dashboard-app/src/components/time/time-entries-list.tsx#308-760) - shows break only if gap > 60 seconds
**Issue**: This is correct! Breaks SHOULD only show for gaps > 1 minute
**Action**: Verify this is working as expected - might not be a bug

### 3. Entries Splitting When They Should Merge ❌ **CRITICAL**
**Problem**: 
- Entry 1: ends at 01:02
- Entry 2: starts at 01:02  
- Same project + same task
- They appear as 2 separate entries instead of merging into one

**Root Cause**: [finalizeActiveToEntry()](file:///c:/Users/oleks/dashboard-app/src/app/dashboard/time/actions.ts#174-208) (line 179) creates new entry without checking if it can merge with previous entry

**Solution**: Add merge logic to [finalizeActiveToEntry()](file:///c:/Users/oleks/dashboard-app/src/app/dashboard/time/actions.ts#174-208)

## Implementation Plan

### Step 1: Add Merge Logic to [finalizeActiveToEntry()](file:///c:/Users/oleks/dashboard-app/src/app/dashboard/time/actions.ts#174-208)
**File**: [src/app/dashboard/time/actions.ts](file:///c:/Users/oleks/dashboard-app/src/app/dashboard/time/actions.ts)

Before creating new entry, check:
1. Find most recent entry for this user
2. If exists AND:
   - Same `type` (work/work)
   - Same `projectId` 
   - Same `taskId`
   - `previousEntry.endAt` == `newEntry.startAt` (touching times)
   - Gap between them <= 60 seconds
3. Then: **UPDATE** previous entry's `endAt` and `durationSec` instead of creating new one

**Pseudo-code**:
```typescript
async function finalizeActiveToEntry(userId: string) {
  const active = await prisma.activeTimer.findUnique({ where: { userId } });
  if (!active) return null;

  const endedAt = now();
  const durationSec = secondsBetween(active.startedAt, endedAt);

  if (durationSec < MIN_ENTRY_SECONDS) {
    await prisma.activeTimer.delete({ where: { userId } });
    return { created: false, reason: "too_short", durationSec };
  }

  // NEW: Try to merge with previous entry
  const previousEntry = await prisma.timeEntry.findFirst({
    where: { userId },
    orderBy: { endAt: 'desc' },
    take: 1,
  });

  const canMerge = previousEntry && 
    previousEntry.type === active.mode &&
    previousEntry.projectId === (active.mode === 'work' ? active.projectId : null) &&
    previousEntry.taskId === (active.mode === 'work' ? active.taskId : null) &&
    previousEntry.endAt &&
    Math.abs(previousEntry.endAt.getTime() - active.startedAt.getTime()) <= 60000; // 1 min tolerance

  if (canMerge) {
    // Merge: extend previous entry
    const newDuration = secondsBetween(previousEntry.startAt, endedAt);
    await prisma.timeEntry.update({
      where: { id: previousEntry.id },
      data: {
        endAt: endedAt,
        durationSec: newDuration,
      },
    });
    await prisma.activeTimer.delete({ where: { userId } });
    return { created: false, merged: true, durationSec: newDuration };
  }

  // Create new entry (existing logic)
  await prisma.timeEntry.create({ ... });
  await prisma.activeTimer.delete({ where: { userId } });
  return { created: true, durationSec };
}
```

### Step 2: Verify Timeline Rendering
Check if `timelineEntries` correctly filters work entries

### Step 3: Test All Scenarios
- [ ] Start work → stop → start same project/task immediately → should merge
- [ ] Start work → stop → wait 2 min → start same project/task → should NOT merge (break shows)
- [ ] Start work → stop → start different project → should NOT merge
- [ ] Timeline shows all entries correctly
